<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="DisableWebmin" version="5.0">
 <title xml:id="SysMgmtServices">Disable Webmin</title>
 <para>
  <application>Webmin</application> allows remote administration over
  HTTP. <application>Webmin</application>, and other tools like it, can
  be dangerous as they have a history of bad authentication or session
  management.
  <indexterm>
   <primary>Webmin</primary>
  </indexterm>
 </para>
 <para>
  <application>Webmin</application> is part of Solaris by default, but
  is disabled. However, it is not part of Red Hat Enterprise Linux by
  default. It is highly recommended to apply this module.
 </para>
